<div class="comment-wrapper"><ul class="comments"><li class="comment"><div class="avatar"><img src="https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/886f7902c986a59d5cc184425d513c36?s=50"></div><header><strong>[Pitch] Rename `index(of:)` and `index(where:)` to `firstIndex(of:)` and `firstIndex(where:)` respectively</strong> from <string>Tim Vermeulen</string> &lt;tvermeulen at me.com&gt;<p>July 24, 2016 at 11:00:00am</p></header><div class="content"><p>`firstIndex` is completely unambiguous, whereas with `index` people might wonder which index is returned. Also, if `lastIndex` methods ever get added to the standard library, they will be a lot more consistent with `firstIndex` than with `index`.<br></p><p>On the other hand, `index` is short and simple, and people might not care whether it is the first index that matches or a different one. Still I think `firstIndex` is more in line with the naming guidelines.<br></p><p>Thoughts?<br></p></div><ul class="comments"><li class="comment"><div class="avatar"><img src="https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/76dd8f23593c1a1f5c57cc6a8982d726?s=50"></div><header><strong>[Pitch] Rename `index(of:)` and `index(where:)` to `firstIndex(of:)` and `firstIndex(where:)` respectively</strong> from <string>Brent Royal-Gordon</string> &lt;brent at architechies.com&gt;<p>July 24, 2016 at 08:00:00am</p></header><div class="content"><p>&gt; On Jul 24, 2016, at 2:58 AM, Tim Vermeulen via swift-evolution &lt;swift-evolution at swift.org&gt; wrote:<br>&gt; <br>&gt; `firstIndex` is completely unambiguous, whereas with `index` people might wonder which index is returned. Also, if `lastIndex` methods ever get added to the standard library, they will be a lot more consistent with `firstIndex` than with `index`.<br>&gt; <br>&gt; On the other hand, `index` is short and simple, and people might not care whether it is the first index that matches or a different one. Still I think `firstIndex` is more in line with the naming guidelines.<br>&gt; <br>&gt; Thoughts?<br></p><p>Wor